	if (($_REQUEST["PPID"]) == 2) {
		$strMainCopy	=	"<h1>Abi & Chris Corfu wedding 2009</h1>
<p>Abi and Chris had a very special wedding in Corfu in the summer of 2009. The ceremony took place at the heart of the historic town and it was followed by waterfront reception inside the Venetian Old Fortress. They both regularly go abroad as Chris is a pilot and Abi cabin crew, so a dream wedding in the Greek islands was not a difficult decision. In the interview below, they describe their experience, how they met and why they chose Corfu over so many other exotic destinations.</p>
<h2>Did you meet during a flight? Is &quot;cabin romance&quot; something that happens a lot?</h2>
<p>We flew together to Catania, Sicily so we met somewhere above the French Alps.  I had always said I would never date a pilot so, never say never!!! We have quite a few friends now who have met onboard as crew and are now married or getting married.</p>
<h2>Was the proposal during a flight? Please give details</h2>
<p>As we met above the Alps, Chris took me to Morzine skiing and arranged for a horse drawn sleigh to take us on a ride and stop at a viewpoint so that Chris could propose to me.  It was how I had always envisaged my wedding to be, on a snowy mountain, but to be proposed to that way was perfect.</p>
<h2>Why did you choose Corfu over the many exotic destinations you fly to?</h2>
<p>Corfu has always had a special place in my heart.  This year was my 25th year of visiting Corfu as I have family that live there.  Chris had been with me once on the QE2 which was amazing and then again on a 2 week holiday and he too fell in love with the Island.  It's so relaxing; the scenery is stunning and the locals so welcoming.  Yes we do fly to many exotic destinations but whenever friends or indeed passengers ask me my favourite destination, Corfu always wins.</p>
<h2>What is the feeling you get as cabin crew when you approach Corfu?</h2>
<p>I have operated into Corfu many times with a previous airline and have landed in all kinds of weather which can make it interesting, but this time when we landed it was a very exciting time as I knew it was the last time I would be landing anywhere in the world as Miss Abi Ballam.</p>
<h2>Did you build into the wedding plans anything to remind you of what you do?</h2>
<p>I had a professional cake topper made of the pair of us.  Chris in his pilot's uniform and myself in my wedding dress.  I just had to send her some pictures of Chris in his uniform. It turned out brilliantly.</p>
<h2>Would you say that you had an edge over other brides because of your knowledge of the travel industry?</h2>
<p>No not really, we entrusted Ionian Weddings to take care of everything and you did a brilliant job.  With regular flights throughout the summer popping over before the wedding is something I would recommend if you have the time and money.  It helped ease the pre-wedding nerves.</p>
<h2>Was it helpful that you decided to get married short haul?</h2>
<p>We thought that a lot more guests would be unable to come to Corfu due to the credit crunch but we were pleasantly surprised out of 75 invites we had 69 guests.  I think making it a short haul destination definitely helped our guests manage to afford to come.</p>
<h2>What would you advise brides that wish to marry abroad?</h2>
<p>Put your trust into the hands of Ionian Weddings. They arrange weddings everyday and are available by email or at the end of the phone if you need reassurance.  I must admit I was a little stressed due to the language barrier dealing with locals over the phone but face to face and email was much easier.  This needn't happen if you leave everything to the professional care of the Ionian Weddings team, that's what they are there for!</p>";
	}
	if (($_REQUEST["PPID"]) == 3) {
		$strMainCopy	=	"<h1>Tara & Paul Kos wedding June 2009</h1>
<h2>How did you two meet and where did the proposal take place?</h2>
<p>We met 13 years ago at my first job at Heathrow; Paul was one of my directors!  I fell in love with him the first day I met him, when I was greeted with a big smile, a cup of coffee and the morning paper, 2 minutes after I had sat at my desk!  WHAT A LOVELY START TO MY FIRST JOB!</p>
<p>The proposal took place at the Basilica ruins opposite St Stefanos Island where we eventually got married (about 6 years before the wedding!) Paul got down on one knee on a beautiful day in Kefalos, asked me to be his wife and said he would marry me over the water at the little church on the island one day!</p>
<h2>Why did you choose Greece and Kos for your wedding?</h2>
<p>We started travelling to Kos a year after meeting each other and apart from a couple of exceptions have been travelling there every year since; we love Kos, especially Kefalos.</p>
<h2>Was it your first time in Kos?  What did you think?</h2>
<p>We booked a last minute holiday and arrived in Kefalos at lunchtime on a Saturday.  We were very tired from the early start but couldn't help exploring the place when we got there.  The majority of everything is on the waterfront, and we are BIG lovers of the sea, so Kefalos is our most perfect place in the world to relax and while away the hours watching the sun go down over the harbour.</p>
<h2>How did you prepare for your wedding in Greece? Was it was you expected?</h2>
<p>As I said before we had always wanted to get married on the little island and had seen just a few weddings take place there over the years.  I had searched and searched for someone to organise if for us when I came upon Ionian Weddings who had my dream wedding idea on their site after 6 years of searching!!</p>
<h2>Please describe the most memorable moment from your big day.</h2>
<p>I can honestly say the whole day was so perfect there wasn't one moment that stood out as the most memorable, the whole day was!</p>
<h2>Is there anything quirky or funny that reminds you of your Greek wedding experience?</h2>
<p>My auntie Margaret missing the coach and the boat and frantically searched every harbour in Kos to find the wedding, and eventually found Kefalos and persuaded a local to take her and her partner Gary across to the Island for the ceremony!</p>
<h2>What advice would you give to other brides considering getting married in Greece?</h2>
<p>Greece is such a perfect place to marry because of its outstanding beauty in the country itself, its people and its traditions.  Kos is especially beautiful, namely Kefalos, the St Stefanos wedding provides an unforgettable setting that you, your family and your guests will treasure forever.</p>
<p>I would just like to add how fantastic Ionian Weddings were here in the UK and their calming approach on all the prep before. You helped calm my wedding nerves every step of the way, taking every bit of stress of a wedding away from me! And finally the local team in Kos, I wasn't the easiest to deal with, as I am a stickler for detail, but Ionian Weddings had everything under control and the rest of the team were professional throughout and great fun on the day!</p>";
	}
	if (($_REQUEST["PPID"]) == 4) {
		$strMainCopy	=	"<h1>Catherine & Carl Zakythos wedding August 2009</h1>
<h2>How did you two meet and where did the proposal take place?</h2>
<p>We actually met on Facebook. Started talking and went out for a drink. Nine hours later, we were still in the pub. It was a good first date! The first proposal took place in a beer garden at a local folk festival then after asking for my dad's permission, the second took place in Dublin. That was 4 months after we met.</p>
<h2>Why did you choose Greece and Zakynthos for your wedding? And why Agios Sostis Island?</h2>
<p>We really wanted to get married on the beach and ideally wanted somewhere short haul so more of our friends could come. Greece is such a beautiful country so we were really happy when we found out we could get married there. Agios Sostis island looked truly breathtaking and knowing that we could hire it exclusively, allowing us to have privacy during our ceremony made it an easy choice.</p>
<h2>Was it your first time in Zante?  What did you think?</h2>
<p>We travelled to Zante the year before the wedding to have a look at the private Island, the reception venues and to meet up with the local coordinator. At the end of the holiday, we knew we had made the right choice about getting married on Zante and Agios Sostis Island with Ionian Weddings.</p>
<h2>How did your guests react to your wedding in Greece? And after?</h2>
<p>They thought it was the most amazing wedding location ever. They loved the island of Zante and lots of them are planning to return, including us!</p>
<h2>Please describe the most memorable moment from your big day.</h2>
<p>The ceremony took place in the evening so we had spent the evening before and the whole day apart. Seeing each other for the first time on our wedding day was very special and something we will both remember. It was emotional.</p>
<h2>Is there anything quirky or funny that reminds you of your Greek wedding experience?</h2>
<p>We chartered a boat a couple of days before the wedding and the captain turned up at the ceremony. In the group shot of all our friends, you can just make out Panos the boat captain behind one of our friends.</p>
<h2>What advice would you give to other brides considering getting married in Greece?</h2>
<p>If you want a truly unique and romantic location that you will remember for the rest of your life, then you can't do better than Agios Sostis Island. Ionian Weddings were so helpful in planning every detail. We were initially worried about the relaxed approach to doing things in the Mediterranean but after dealing with Ionian Weddings, I knew we would have no problems. It was a truly amazing day and we thank everyone involved from the bottom of our hearts for making the best day of our lives, the best it could be.</p>";
